<br>
I did my own calculations on this some years ago and concluded that we would need (In the UK) around 200 power reactors on-line by 2050 in order to cope with the collapse of oil and gas production.<br>
<br>
One cannot engage in this sort of project all in one go, and one certainly will not be able to do it if we wait until we need to for we simply wont have the resources.<br>
<br>
Indeed it may already be too late. In order to have this plant on line in time we needed to start building (at a rate of 5 new plants a year, every year!) 3 years ago!<br>
